Description: Small fragment of a seal-impression, the rear shows a curved surface as from a leather bag. The fine brown Nile clay has few inclusions of mica and was hardened after excavation, the surface is partly shiny. At the front a small part of an impression of a scarab-like seal is visible as well as finger prints around it. The seal is not recognisable, it could show two parallel lines.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
